HEADWORD: kiaat
<hw>kiaat</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a deciduous South African tree
(<spn>Pterocarpus angolensis</spn>) having large odd-pinnate leaves and
profuse fragrant orange-yellow flowers; it yields a red juice and heavy
strong durable wood.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bloodwood tree, <spn>Pterocarpus
angolensis</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kiabooca wood</ent>⟦br⟧
